If running Linux, use the gimptool command:

$ gimptool --install-script <your script name>

Or look under the ~/.gimp/scripts folder. If running Windows, look under %HOME%\.gimp\scripts, or under %USERPROFILE%\.gimp\scripts if %HOME% is not defined. Put the lomo-gimp.scm file there. Then restart the GIMP or do a refresh by using Xtns, Script-Fu, Refresh Scripts from the toolbox. The script will now appear in the Script-Fu, Alchemy menu.

Find more scripts at registry.gimp.org .
